{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Q3ndAytZKbvn2rPNkvx85o","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a Python function that removes all script tags and their contents from HTML content using regex. I should write this to `candidate.py`.\n\nThe task is straightforward:\n1. Create a function that takes a string as input\n2. Use regex to remove all `<script>...</script>` tags and their contents\n3. Return the modified string\n\nI need to be careful with the regex pattern:\n- I need to match `<script` (case-insensitive is probably good)\n- Then match anything up to `</script>` (including the closing tag)\n- The content inside can have newlines, so I need the DOTALL flag (or use [\\s\\S])\n\nA good regex pattern would be:\n- `<script[^>]*>.*?</script>` - but this won't match newlines by default\n- `<script[^>]*>.*?</script>` with `re.DOTALL` flag would work\n- Or `<script[^>]*>[\\s\\S]*?</script>` without needing DOTALL\n\nI should also consider:\n- Case insensitivity (Script, SCRIPT, etc.)\n- Multiple script tags\n- Newlines and whitespace in the script content\n\nLet me write a clean solution:\n\n```python\nimport re\n\ndef remove_script_tags(html):\n    \"\"\"Remove all script tags and their contents from HTML content.\"\"\"\n    return re.sub(r'<script[^>]*>.*?</script>', '', html, flags=re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL)\n```\n\nThis uses:\n- `<script[^>]*>` - matches opening script tag with any attributes\n- `.*?` - matches any content (non-greedy)\n- `</script>` - matches closing script tag\n- `re.IGNORECASE` - handles Script, SCRIPT, etc.\n- `re.DOTALL` - makes . match newlines as well\n\n\n- The non-greedy matching ensures we stop at the first `</script>` rather than the last one, which handles edge cases like `>` characters in script content correctly. Even with malformed HTML, the regex will still remove the tags as intended.\n\nNow I'll implement this solution with the regex pattern using both `re.IGNORECASE` and `re.DOTALL` flags to handle case variations and multiline scripts.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4658,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4658},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9eccf652-4aca-4db2-97f7-f6a89af744b0","uuid":"3ecc0991-10d8-4087-87ba-d3d64cc94002","request_id":"req_011CbdNAtg6gbc9T4Tpbnw4M"}
